commText: Welcome back.. Travis Head is the impact sub for SRH, he replaces Natarajan. Arshdeep comes in for PBKS, replacing Ashutosh Sharma. He has the new ball and will start proceedings. One slip in place. We are ready to go

214/5 is the highest score for PBKS against SRH, bettering 211/4 in a successful run-chase at the same venue in 2014. Most 200-plus totals in a Men’s T20 competition 42 - T20 Blast 2023 40 - T20 Blast 2022 40 - IPL 2024 37 - IPL 2023
Most sixes for PBKS in an IPL season 127 in 2014 120 in 2024 117 in 2023 110 in 2019 110 in 2022
Captains with most wickets in an IPL season 19 - Shane Warne (RR, 2008) 17 - Anil Kumble (RCB, 2010) 15 - Ravichandran Ashwin (PBKS, 2019) 15 - Pat Cummins (SRH, 2024) 14 - Shane Warne (RR, 2009)

Atharva Taide: It was coming onto the bat nicely and I think we put up a good score. I had some butterflies early on, but as I saw the wicket felt comfortable and I felt I should have scored more. We feel it is a new ball game, and we can pick up a few wickets in the powerplay, we can be ahead in the game. The ball is gripping and I feel we can restrict them.

17:14 Local Time, 11:44 GMT: Punjab Kings would be slightly disappointed with the total despite getting 19 off the final over. They got only 40 runs from the last 4 overs. Prabhsimran and Taide started brilliantly by taking on the bowling and adding a 97-run stand, Rossouw came out and continued to attack, there was another 50+ stand for the second wicket. At 174/2 in 16 overs, Punjab would have expected a better finish and a score around 220-230 but they lost their set batters and if not for that last over assault from Jitesh, they would have fallen well short of a par total. Sunrisers are not known for their chasing, apart from the Lucknow game, and this will be a good test for them before the big playoff games. Back soon with the chase..

Nitish Reddy to Jitesh Sharma, SIX, Jitesh finishes with a maximum. Another slower ball dug into the surface, Jitesh stays leg-side and has the room to free his arms, slaps it high and gets it to cross the extra cover fence

Nitish Reddy to Jitesh Sharma, SIX, that's a gift and Jitesh makes the most of it. High full toss just bekow the waist, the line was also on leg-stump and Jitesh just had to make a good connection, he swings hard and sends it sailing over deep square leg
Nitish Reddy to Jitesh Sharma, wide, slower bumper and Jitesh tries his best to connect with the hook, too high and it is deemed a wide
Nitish Reddy to Jitesh Sharma, FOUR, in the air and the ball lands in the gap. Jitesh gives the charge and gets a full toss on the pads, heaves it right between deep mid-wicket and long-on
Nitish Reddy to Shivam Singh, 1 run, another slower ball bowled into the wicket, Shivam gets a top-edge on the pull and the ball lands in front of fine leg
Nitish Reddy to Shivam Singh, no run, I0$ off-pace short of length delivery, Shivam attempts a fancy reverse lap but does not make contact

Nitish Reddy to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, I0$ short of length delivery, Jitesh pulls it straight to deep square leg. There was a collision between Jitesh and Nitish as both were watching the ball, no harm done
Nitish Reddy [2.0-0-35-0] is back into the attack

T Natarajan to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, I0$ short of length delivery, Jitesh is rushed on the pull and miscues it to square leg, Natarajan races across to take the catch but can get there only on the bounce
T Natarajan to Jitesh Sharma, no run, off-pace delivery bowled into the wicket, Jitesh waited to play the crossed batted shot but still could not connect
T Natarajan to Jitesh Sharma, 2 runs, fullish delivery around off, Jitesh sweeps to deep mid-wicket and Nitish fumbles, Shivam calls for the second and puts in the dive to make his ground
T Natarajan to Jitesh Sharma, FOUR, much needed. Slower ball and this one sits up outside off, Jitesh stands tall and slaps it over extra cover, one bounce and over the ropes
T Natarajan to Shivam Singh, 1 run, slower short of length delivery, Shivam waits and pulls to deep mid-wicket
Shivam Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease

T Natarajan to Ashutosh Sharma, out Caught by Sanvir Singh!! That's an excellent catch. Punjab lose another and are losing their way at the back end of the innings. Slower ball from Natarajan and Ashutosh goes for the big shot, miscues it off the outer half over extra cover and Sanvir runs back, takes it over his head and hits the ground hard but the ball stays firmly in his grasp. Ashutosh Sharma c Sanvir Singh b T Natarajan 2(3)
T Natarajan to Ashutosh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
T Natarajan to Ashutosh Sharma, wide, strays down leg and Ashutosh cannot make contact with the glance, wide called
T Natarajan [3.0-0-24-1] is back into the attack
Cummins to Jitesh Sharma, 2 runs, I0$ slower ball bowled into the wicket, Jitesh makes room and slaps it in front of square, Nitish gets around from sweeper cover and keeps it down to a brace
Cummins to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, I0$ off-pace delivery and Ashutosh dabs it off the glove to point
Cummins to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, I0$ full pitcher on off, Jitesh drives to mid-off and takes on Samad, he would have made it in even with a direct hit
Cummins to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, good length ball around off, Ashutosh knocks it into the off-side and gets off the mark
Ashutosh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Cummins to Rossouw, out Caught by Abdul Samad!! This is a massive wicket. Rossouw had to be there till then but instead he falls one short of his fifty. This was not a wicket-taking delivery - full toss around the knee, Rossouw swings hard and does not time it at all, Samad runs in from long-on and picks up an easy catch. Rossouw c Abdul Samad b Cummins 49(24) [4s-3 6s-4]
Cummins to Rossouw, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Round the wicket to Rossouw
Cummins to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, slower ball outside off, Jitesh drags the heave to long-on and it is only a single
Pat Cummins [3.0-0-30-0] is back into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, I0$ full delivery on leg, Jitesh flicks to deep mid-wicket and retains strike
Bhuvneshwar to Jitesh Sharma, no run, high full toss just below the waist, Jitesh gets the drive high on the bat and the ball goes straight to cover
Bhuvneshwar to Jitesh Sharma, 2 runs, speared into the blockhole, Jitesh jams it between deep mid-wicket and long-on, easy brace
Bhuvneshwar to Rossouw, 1 run, full toss and Rossouw feels missed out, it was at a good height as well and he miscues the heave to long-on
Bhuvneshwar to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, full on off, drilled down to long-off
Bhuvneshwar to Rossouw, 1 run, full and angled in at the pads, clipped away to the left of deep mid-wicket
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [3.0-0-30-0] is back into the attack
Jitesh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Timeout! Punjab have the platform laid and now have to finish strongly. Rossouw will be the key in the last four overs. SRH need to continue picking wickets..

Nitish Reddy to Shashank Singh, out Shashank Singh Run Out!! 1 run completed. What happened there? Miscommunication and Shashank is gone. Slower back of a length delivery, Shashank nudges it to the vacant mid-wicket region and Nitish chases after it, the batters always wanted a brace and Rossouw went for it, but Shashank hesitated and that cost him. He started to go for the second but stopped and then had to sacrifice himself as Rossouw was more than halfway down. Nitish fumbled to collect the ball and that might have put doubts in the two batters. Shashank Singh run out (Nitish Reddy/Klaasen) 2(4)
Nitish Reddy to Shashank Singh, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!
Nitish Reddy to Shashank Singh, no run, I0$ back of a length delivery, Shashank gets inside the line and helps it straight to short fine
Nitish Reddy to Rossouw, 1 run, slower short of length delivery, Rossouw jabs it to deep mid-wicket

Nitish Reddy to Rossouw, FOUR, Nitish Reddy is being taken to the cleaners. Rossouw advances and though the length was short, he had the width to slap it in front of square and beat long-off in the deep
Nitish Reddy to Rossouw, wide, off-pace delivery and it is sprayed outside off, Rossouw ignores and collects the wide

Nitish Reddy to Rossouw, SIX, flat and travels the distance. Slower ball angled across, Rossouw maintains a solid pace and smokes it over deep mid-wicket. That ball hardly left the ground but ended up over the rope
Nitish Reddy to Rossouw, 2 runs, short of length delivery and Rossouw does not quite get hold of the pull, mistimed to the left of long-on and it is just brace
Nitish Reddy [1.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack

Over Summary (11-15) -> Prabhsimran Singh notches up his fifty off 34 balls -> Reddy bowls an expensive over, concedes 20 runs -> Rossouw off to a brisk start -> Viyaskanth removes the set batter, Prabhsimran is out for 71
Prabhsimran vs SRH in the IPL \nBefore today: 5 inns, 45 runs, Avg: 9, SR: 104.65, HS: 16 \nToday: 71 off 45, SR: 157.78

V Viyaskanth to Rossouw, leg byes, 1 run, appeal for LBW. But no review taken. This was the googly and Rossouw did not pick it, he's rooted to the crease and plays down the wrong line, gets beaten on the outside edge and is struck on the back pad. Luckily the ball had pitched outside leg and hence he survives
Going back to Prabhsimran's wicket: The UltraEdge was used and there was the smallest of murmurs. But the third umpire was confident that the ball brushed the glove and went with the onfield call.
V Viyaskanth to Rossouw, SIX, dragged short and Rossouw is quick to pounce, he rocks back and nails the pull over deep mid-wicket
V Viyaskanth to Shashank Singh, 1 run, turned with soft hands to the leg-side and Shashank quickly crosses over
V Viyaskanth to Shashank Singh, no run, comes down the track and is not to the pitch of the ball, defended to the off-side
Shashank Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease

V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Klaasen!! That's an unfortunate way to depart. But SRH are not complaining as they have removed the set batter. Prabhsimran moved away and Viyaskanth followed him with a quicker delivery, the heave is not connected and the ball hits the pad down leg, lobs up and brushes the glove, Klaasen moves ahead of the stumps and dives forward to scoop up the catch. Prabhsimran c Klaasen b V Viyaskanth 71(45) [4s-7 6s-4]
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Punjab review! Prabhsimran is given out caught behind but he has challenged the decision immediately. This seems to have come off the pad. Or did it hit the glove on the way? "There's a clear spike when ball is next to the glove," reckons umpire Saiyed Khalid. OUT!

V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, no run, some turn for Viyaskanth. The length is short and Prabhsimran has a hack across the line, the ball spins away to beat his swinging blade and wasn't far from the off-stump
Vijayakanth Viyaskanth [3.0-0-30-0] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Rossouw, no run, I0$ full pitcher outside off, Rossouw drives and picks out extra cover
T Natarajan to Prabhsimran, 1 run, charges down and is met by a shortened length, punches it to mid-off and has to hurry. Cummins has a shy at the bowler's end but the throw was not on target
T Natarajan to Rossouw, 1 run, short and banged into the wicket, Rossouw pulls in front of square and settles with a single
T Natarajan to Prabhsimran, 1 run, I0$ low full toss on off, Prabhsimran toe-ends the drive to mid-off
T Natarajan to Rossouw, 1 run, full and angled into the pads, Rossouw flicks to deep square leg
T Natarajan to Rossouw, SIX, smashed! This was a slot ball - full and right in the arc, Rossouw gets his front leg out of the way and pumps it over long-on. That brings up the 50-run stand..
T Natarajan to Rossouw, wide, goes for the slower bouncer but too short and too high, called for height
T Natarajan [2.0-0-13-1] is back into the attack
Cummins to Rossouw, 1 run, yorker length at I0$ on the stumps, Rossouw squeezes it along the ground through mid-wicket
Cummins to Rossouw, FOUR, slower length ball at I0$ sits up nicely outside off, Rossouw goes deep inside the crease and thrashes the pull in the gap between deep mid-wicket and wide long-on
Cummins to Prabhsimran, 1 run, I0$ full toss outside off, Prabhsimran looks to go hard and mistimes it off the toe end to the left of sweeper cover
Cummins to Prabhsimran, FOUR, premeditates the scoop and shuffles a long way across to drag the slower short ball past Bhuvi at short fine to his right
Cummins to Prabhsimran, no run, slower length delivery outside off, Prabhsimran cuts and finds the fielder at backward point
Cummins to Rossouw, 1 run, I0$ full toss at the hip, Rossouw swats and gets it off the thick inside half to the left of deep square
Pat Cummins [2.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Nitish Reddy to Rossouw, 1 run, advances and slaps the slower full delivery down to long-off. 20 off the over
Nitish Reddy to Prabhsimran, 1 run, sees Prabhsimran dancing down and sends in a slower full delivery wide of off, Prabhsimran reaches out and squeezes it into the covers
Nitish Reddy to Prabhsimran, SIX, Prabhsimran walks across, gets inside the line of a short ball and helps the pull into the fine leg stands for another mighty maximum
Nitish Reddy to Rossouw, 1 run, full on leg stump at I0$, flicked away to deep square
Nitish Reddy to Rossouw, SIX, Nitish Reddy goes short once again and Rossouw has nailed the pull for a 69-metre maximum over mid-wicket
Nitish Reddy to Rossouw, FOUR, shortens the length and keeps it wide of off, Rossouw swivels and mauls the pull over mid-wicket for a one-bounce boundary
Nitish Reddy to Rossouw, no ball, Nitish Reddy oversteps and bowls a fuller length delivery wide of off, Rossouw lets it pass
Nitish Reddy, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, no run, quicker on the stumps, Prabhsimran looks to slog and gets beaten on the outside edge. Mild appeal for caught behind, but no dice...
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, SIX, floaty full delivery outside off, Prabhsimran gets under it and lofts it many-a-mile over long-on
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, 2 runs, worked away to the right of long-on and that will be fifty for Prabhsimran Singh. A raise of the bat and then a handshake from his partner...
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, no run, flat on off, punched back to the bowler
V Viyaskanth to Rossouw, 1 run, quicker and just outside off, Rossouw opens the bat face and stabs it to the right of backward point
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, 1 run, full on leg stump, clipped away to deep square

Over Summary (6-10) -> A productive powerplay for Punjab Kings, 61/0 -> Runs coming thick and fast for the Kings -> Shahbaz Ahmed bowls an expensive over, goes for 13 runs -> Natarajan breaks the partnership, Taide is caught at backward point -> Punjab Kings - 99/1 (10 overs) - a lovely over by Natarajan
T Natarajan to Rossouw, no run, looks to slog a I0$ length delivery and gets beaten on the under edge. Wasn't too far from the off stump either...
T Natarajan to Prabhsimran, 1 run, I0$ back of a length outside off, Prabhsimran shuffles and heaves it into the vacant mid-wicket space
T Natarajan to Prabhsimran, no run, slower ball bumper outside off, Prabhsimran looks to pull and ends up dragging it off the cue end back towards the bowler
T Natarajan to Prabhsimran, no run, slower back of a length delivery outside off, Prabhsimran looks to cut and mistimes it to the left of backward point
T Natarajan to Rossouw, 1 run, pitched up outside off, driven down to long-on
Rilee Rossouw, left handed bat, comes to the crease

T Natarajan to Atharva Taide, out Caught by Sanvir Singh!! There's the breakthrough for SRH. Natarajan goes short and wide of off, Taide has looked good but has looked pretty static (lack of feet) at times. He went for the cut but lack of feet meant, he chipped it straght to backward point off the thick inside half. Atharva Taide c Sanvir Singh b T Natarajan 46(27) [4s-5 6s-2]
T Natarajan to Atharva Taide, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
T Natarajan [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
V Viyaskanth to Atharva Taide, 1 run, quicker on leg stump, clipped away to deep mid-wicket
V Viyaskanth to Atharva Taide, FOUR, floated up nicely on the stumps, Taide lifts the drive back over the bowler's head and beats the fielder in the deep to his left
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, 1 run, quicker just outside off, knocked away into the leg-side for an easy single
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, leg byes, 2 runs, full and drifting down leg, Prabhsimran misses the flick and it runs away off the boot to the right of short fine

Shahbaz Ahmed to Atharva Taide, 1 run, short on leg stump, Taide swivels and pulls to the left of deep mid-wicket
Shahbaz Ahmed to Atharva Taide, no run, short outside off, no feet from Taide as he slaps and finds extra cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Prabhsimran, 1 run, slower and just outside off, Prabhsimran works it into the mid-wicket pocket
Shahbaz Ahmed to Atharva Taide, 1 run, short and wide of off, Atharva goes deep inside the crease and cuts to the right of sweeper cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Atharva Taide, SIX, quicker and flatter on leg stump, Atharva dances down the wicket and wallops Shahbaz Ahmed into the deep mid-wicket orbit
Shahbaz Ahmed to Atharva Taide, FOUR, Taide goes for the reverse sweep now. Premeditated shot and he's connected that well enough to beat short third to his right
Shahbaz Ahmed, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, 2 runs, excellent fielding effort from Nitish Reddy. Surely saved a boundary there. Prabhsimran timed the slogsweep really well and the fielder from wide long-on ran a long way across before flicking the ball back into play despite the momentum taking him beyond the ropes
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, no run, quick and short on off, Prabhsimran chops and finds backward point
"It's gotten slightly dark at Uppal with some grey clouds overhead. They are starting to turn the floodlights on." - pings Gokul from the ground.
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, no run, short outside off, cut away to backward point
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, FOUR, floaty full delivery outside off, Prabhsimran gets under it and launches it back over the bowler's head for his 6th boundary
V Viyaskanth to Atharva Taide, 1 run, quicker and wider of off, cut away to the right of sweeper cover
STAT: 61* between Prabhsimran and Taide is the highest opening stand for PBKS against SRH, bettering 55 (in 7.5 overs) between Chris Gayle and KL Rahul at the same venue in 2018.
V Viyaskanth to Prabhsimran, leg byes, 1 run, starts off with a quicker delivery on leg stump, Prabhsimran misses the flick and it rolls away off the thigh pad to short fine
Vijayakanth Viyaskanth, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack

Timeout! Not a great deal of movement for the bowlers and the Punjab openers have done well to not lose wickets inside the powerplay. Both openers have got starts and expect one of these two to press on the accelerator pretty soon...
Bhuvneshwar to Atharva Taide, SIX, launched! Length ball in the slot outside off, Taide clears his front leg and swats the pull over cow corner with terrific timing

Bhuvneshwar to Atharva Taide, leg byes, 1 run, looks to go leg-side once again and gets beaten by the lack of bounce on this, takes the thigh pad and rolls to square leg

Over Summary (1-5) -> A tidy start by Cummins and Bhuvneshwar, only 12 from the first 2 overs -> Bhuvneshwar concedes 12 runs in the third over -> A loose start by Natarajan, concedes a couple of boundaries -> A steady partnership building between PBKS openers - 47/0 (5)

Cummins to Prabhsimran, SIX, picked up off the toes. Full and curling into leg stump at I0$, Prabhsimran hoicks it with brilliant timing and beats the fielder running across to his right from deep square
Cummins to Prabhsimran, FOUR, I0$ short on the stumps, Prabhsimran swivels and powers the pull over mid-wicket

Cummins to Atharva Taide, no run, bumper angling away wide of off at I0$, Taide lets it pass. SRH skipper didn't like the wide call from the umpire and has opted for the review. Replays in: Ball's well inside the guide line and no issue with height as well. Umpire Virender Sharma has to overturn his decision...
Cummins to Prabhsimran, 1 run, full and dips at the toes at I0$, Prabhsimran flicks it to the right of deep square
Pat Cummins [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Atharva Taide, FOUR, 11 off the over. Taide pulls the short ball and gets a thick top-edge that flies over short fine

T Natarajan to Prabhsimran, 1 run, full on the pads, clipped away square on the leg-side
15:45 Local Time, 10:15 GMT: It's drizzling right now, but not bad enough to take the players off the field....
T Natarajan to Prabhsimran, no run, sees Prabhsimran shuffle across early and digs it short at the last moment, Prabhsimran tries to pull but gets beaten on the top-edge
T Natarajan to Atharva Taide, 1 run, I0$ length outside off, Taide stays deep inside the crease and stabs it to deep backward point

T Natarajan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Prabhsimran, 1 run, I0$ good length just outside off, Prabhsimran drops it to the left of cover and hurries across for a quick single
Bhuvneshwar to Prabhsimran, FOUR, Bhuvneshwar shortens the length, but the result doesn't change. Prabhsimran sits on the back foot and muscles the pull over mid-wicket

The keeper is staning upto the stumps for Prabhsimran

Bhuvneshwar to Atharva Taide, 1 run, slower full delivery from Bhuvi. Taide's early into the drive and chips it to the left of the bowler, Bhuvi tries his best with a half-hearted dive but the ball drops well wide of him and rolls to mid-on
Bhuvneshwar to Atharva Taide, no run, I0$ good length on off, punched to the left of mid-off
Bhuvneshwar to Atharva Taide, 2 runs, short of length on middle and leg, clipped away square on the leg-side
Cummins to Prabhsimran, no run, charges down the pitch and stabs the length delivery to the left of Samad at extra cover

Cummins to Prabhsimran, no run, 149.4ks from the SRH skipper. Goes full and sprays it around leg stump to catch Prabhsimran in front of the stumps, appeal for leg before but that's missing leg comfortably

Bhuvneshwar to Prabhsimran, no run, back of a length on off at I0$, Prabhsimran hops and tucks into the leg-side

Atharva Taide and Prabhsimran are at the crease. Atharva Taide is on strike. Bhuvneshwar will open the attack
